lass=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 30, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xdm1665703133890.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xdm1665703133890.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xdm1665703133890.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xdm1665703133890\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__ugettxtc_404006\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Get additional data from a Uniface message or help text.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__topic_d120761e1_d120762e1_d120763e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104xdm1665703133890_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__codeblock_pcm_yp1_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">long ugettxtc (unsigned char* buffer, long max);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__topic_d85822e1_d85823e1_d85824e1_d85825e1_d85826e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d100290e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__parml_qn3_zp1_1wb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__p_d120770e1_d120771e1_d120772e1\">(Output) The contents of the message or\n                     help text.</p>\n</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">max</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__p_d120773e1_d120774e1_d120775e1\">The maximum number of characters to be\n                     copied to the buffer pointed to by <var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var>. The size of the\n                     buffer should be at least <var class=\"keyword varname\">max</var>+1 bytes to accommodate the\n                     zero terminator character.</p>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__topic_d85827e1_d85828e1_d85829e1_d85830e1_d85831e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d100290e102\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__d5946e20\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by ugettxt and ugettxtc</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__d5946e20__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__d5946e20__entry__2\">Meaning</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xdm1665703133890__d5946e20__entry__1\">\n&gt;0\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xdm1665703133890__d5946e20__entry__2\">The number of bytes copied into the buffer</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xdm1665703133890__d5946e20__entry__1\">\n0\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xdm1665703133890__d5946e20__entry__2\">An error occurred</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xdm1665703133890__d5946e20__entry__1\">\n&lt;0\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xdm1665703133890__d5946e20__entry__2\">The negated number of bytes copied into the\n                        buffer. The negative status indicates that more data is available in the\n                        field, and that you should call <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxtc</code> to get additional\n                        data. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__topic_d85837e1_d85838e1_d85839e1_d85840e1_d85841e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d100290e166\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__d5947e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">yrtl</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__topic_d85842e1_d85843e1_d85844e1_d85845e1_d85846e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d100290e179\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__p_d120794e1_d120795e1_d120796e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxtc</code> moves an additional chunk\n            of data from a Uniface 4GL message or help text into the specified\n               <var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var>. This function should only be called after a previous call\n            to <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxt</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxtc</code> returned a negative value,\n            which indicates there is more data available.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__p_d120797e1_d120798e1_d120799e1\">Parameters and return values are the same as for\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxt</code>, except there is no parameter for the ID of the message or\n            help text. So if <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxtc</code> also returns a negative status, it must be\n            called repeatedly until a positive status is returned.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__p_d120800e1_d120801e1_d120802e1\">See the \"ugettxt\" topic for additional information\n            and example code.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__section_ljw_fq1_1wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d100290e211\">Example: ugettxt and ugettxtc</h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">The following example retrieves and prints the string value of the\n               message or help text whose <var class=\"keyword varname\">IdString</var> is contained in general\n               register <code class=\"ph codeph\">$1</code>. To illustrate the use of repeated\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugettxtc</code> calls, we read in small chunks and grow the buffer as\n               necessary, in the same way as in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufget</code> / <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufgetc</code>\n               example.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104xdm1665703133890_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"xdm1665703133890__codeblock_b4k_hq1_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">EXPORT void TEST_UGETTXT ()\n{\n#define CHUNKSIZE 12\nchar id[51];\nlong len;\nchar* buf;\nlong totlen;\n\nugetregs(1, (unsigned char *)id, sizeof(id)-1);\nbuf = malloc(CHUNKSIZE);\n\nlen = ugettxt(id, buf, CHUNKSIZE);\ntotlen = abs(len);\n\nwhile ( len &lt; 0 )\n{\nbuf = realloc(buf, totlen+CHUNKSIZE);\nlen = ugettxtc(buf+totlen, CHUNKSIZE);\ntotlen += abs(len);\n}\n\nbuf = realloc(buf, totlen+1);\nbuf[totlen] = 0;\nu_printf(\"The content of id %s is : %s\\n\", id, buf);\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tep1665703133631.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ugettxt</a><p>Get the contents of a message or help text.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533661\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533661\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ugettxtc Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 30, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Get additional data from a Uniface message or help text. Explain this code long ugettxtc (unsigned char* buffer, long max); Copy Parameters buffer (Output) The contents of the message or help text. max The maximum number of characters to be copied to the buffer pointed to by buffer . The size of the buffer should be at least max +1 bytes to accommodate the zero terminator character. Return Values Table 1. Values returned by ugettxt and ugettxtc Value Meaning >0 The number of bytes copied into the buffer 0 An error occurred <0 The negated number of bytes copied into the buffer. The negative status indicates that more data is available in the field, and that you should call ugettxtc to get additional data. Use Library: yrtl Description ugettxtc moves an additional chunk of data from a Uniface 4GL message or help text into the specified buffer . This function should only be called after a previous call to ugettxt or ugettxtc returned a negative value, which indicates there is more data available. Parameters and return values are the same as for ugettxt , except there is no parameter for the ID of the message or help text. So if ugettxtc also returns a negative status, it must be called repeatedly until a positive status is returned. See the \"ugettxt\" topic for additional information and example code. Example: ugettxt and ugettxtc The following example retrieves and prints the string value of the message or help text whose IdString is contained in general register $1 . To illustrate the use of repeated ugettxtc calls, we read in small chunks and grow the buffer as necessary, in the same way as in the ufget / ufgetc example. Explain this code EXPORT void TEST_UGETTXT () { #define CHUNKSIZE 12 char id[51]; long len; char* buf; long totlen; ugetregs(1, (unsigned char *)id, sizeof(id)-1); buf = malloc(CHUNKSIZE); len = ugettxt(id, buf, CHUNKSIZE); totlen = abs(len); while ( len < 0 ) { buf = realloc(buf, totlen+CHUNKSIZE); len = ugettxtc(buf+totlen, CHUNKSIZE); totlen += abs(len); } buf = realloc(buf, totlen+1); buf[totlen] = 0; u_printf(\"The content of id %s is : %s\\n\", id, buf); } Copy Related Links ugettxt Get the contents of a message or help text. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}